review_blob: Grainy smell with pear and cooked vegetable notes. Genuinely amber in the glass with no head retention. Pear, apricot, boiled sweets, husky grain notes, straw. No hop flavors per se but a fairly bitter finish. Fairly flat, watery in the mouth. I like most of the Burleigh beers but this one rubs me up the wrong way. Hardly an IPA.

Pours like watery milk, visible bits of floating rice.  Inviting, sour, somewhat fruity white wine-like nose. Sweet & fruity with noticeable alcohol. Sourness left on the lips,  drier-than-expected finish. Pretty good!
